def plot_image(image, label, fontsize=15, cmap=None, actual=None, predicted=None):
    plt.imshow(image, cmap=cmap)
    if actual is not None and predicted is not None:
        title = f'Actual: {actual}  Predicted: {predicted}'
    else:
        title = label_name.get(label, '')
    plt.title(title, fontsize=fontsize)

# Flattening the images
X_train = X_train.reshape(-1, 28*28)
X_test = X_test.reshape(-1, 28*28)

# Normalizing the data with Min-Max scaling where min is 0 and max is 255
X_train = X_train.astype('float32') / 255

Training Dense Neural Network models¶

In [ ]:
def build_dnn(n_hidden_layers, n_neurons, activation_fn, n_classes):
    hidden_layers = [layers.Dense(n_neurons, activation=activation_fn) for _ in range(n_hidden_layers)]
    output_layer = layers.Dense(n_classes, activation="softmax")

    model = keras.Sequential(hidden_layers + [output_layer])
    model.compile(optimizer="rmsprop",  
              loss="sparse_categorical_crossentropy",
              metrics=["accuracy"])
    return model

configurations = [
    {'n_hidden_layers': 1, 'n_neurons': 512, 'activation_fn': 'tanh', 'batch_size': 256, 'epochs': 10},
    {'n_hidden_layers': 2, 'n_neurons': 512, 'activation_fn': 'relu', 'batch_size': 128, 'epochs': 25},
    {'n_hidden_layers': 2, 'n_neurons': 1024, 'activation_fn': 'relu', 'batch_size': 64, 'epochs': 20}
]
In [ ]:
n_classes = len(np.unique(y_train))
models = []
for i, config in enumerate(configurations):
    print(f'\n{f"  Building Model: {i+1}  ":#^100}')
    for k, v in config.items():
        print(f'{k:<16}: {v}')
    models.append(build_dnn(
        config['n_hidden_layers'], config['n_neurons'], config['activation_fn'], n_classes
    ))
    models[i].fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=config['epochs'], batch_size=config['batch_size'])
